Fur trader (Wallace, Dictionary of Canadian biography). // Bibaud, Michel: 1782-1857. // The original manuscript is in the possession of the Toronto Reference Library. Chapters 24-26 describe Franchère's journey through the prairie region on his return from Astoria. The party travelled via the Saskatchewan River. For English version see Peel 80.
